    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3caa63c4_5448c065",
        "filename": "handler/handler_main.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 401,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-04T02:04:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is intended to install a crash handler for this process, not the target. I think as things are, crashpad_handler crashes will still get caught by the exception port set up by StartHandler since the handler is part of the same job as the client, but then those exceptions will be handled by ExceptionHandlerServer which might be in a bad state. This would be a corollary to crashlogger\u0027s self_dump_port.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 399,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 401,
        "endChar": 43
      },
      "revId": "5cfbdae96e52898b39aa0acc73af22110463258c",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "47bcb3ab_7ae3bc15",
        "filename": "handler/handler_main.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 401,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-04T17:31:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Oh I\u0027m a dope. (Maybe this file\u0027s getting a bit unwieldy too.)\n\nI agree with your expectation of what will happen. I\u0027m not sure we can do a lot better for the in-process case though, so I guess for now a correct comment?",
      "parentUuid": "3caa63c4_5448c065",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 399,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 401,
        "endChar": 43
      },
      "revId": "5cfbdae96e52898b39aa0acc73af22110463258c",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9a5779e0_c7bb01c0",
        "filename": "handler/handler_main.cc",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 401,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-04T19:06:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I agree this file is unwieldy. I remember it taking me several read-through\u0027s to figure out what all these pieces were for.\n\nI think the important thing the other handlers do is just record metrics about why we crashed. i.e. calling MetricsRecordExit() and HandlerCrashed(), with a full-blown MonitorSelf() handler being optional.\n\nI\u0027m also cool with this being a TODO.",
      "parentUuid": "47bcb3ab_7ae3bc15",
